    <fr:title text="the Karoubi envelope">the Karoubi envelope</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C\to \widetilde {C}]]></fr:tex> is said to exhibit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\widetilde {C}]]></fr:tex> as an <html:em>Karoubi envelope</html:em> or <html:em>idempotent completion</html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C\to \widetilde {C}]]></fr:tex> is fully faithful, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\widetilde {C}]]></fr:tex> is idempotent complete, and every object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\widetilde {C}]]></fr:tex> is a retract of (the image of) an object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
